</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[192,1441,265,578]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,342,265,289]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Definition.</emphasis>
A sister to 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1955" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1955" box="[501,779,265,289]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Penicula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[501,610,265,289]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Penicula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[621,779,265,289]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[799,854,266,290]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Weeks, 1906" authorityName="Weeks" authorityYear="1906" box="[965,1368,265,290]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bryanti">
<emphasis box="[965,1192,265,289]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Pamphila bryanti</emphasis>
Weeks, 1906
</taxonomicName>
), this genus is away from 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[441,780,297,322]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Cobalopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[441,575,297,321]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Cobalopsis</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[797,851,298,322]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1891" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1891" box="[954,1325,297,322]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edda">
<emphasis box="[954,1145,297,321]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Pamphila edda</emphasis>
Mabille, 1891
</taxonomicName>
, which is a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Plotz, 1882" authorityName="Plotz" authorityYear="1882" box="[582,962,330,354]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="autumna">
<emphasis box="[582,814,330,353]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Hesperia autumna</emphasis>
Plötz, 1882
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[987,1122,330,354]" captionStart-0="Figure 11" captionStart-1="Figure 12" captionStartId-0="29.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionStartId-1="31.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox-0="[195,1438,214,1295]" captionTargetBox-1="[194,1440,214,1295]" captionTargetId-0="figure@29.[194,1442,213,1296]" captionTargetId-1="figure@31.[192,1440,213,1296]" captionTargetPageId-0="29" captionTargetPageId-1="31" captionText-0="Figure 11. Nuclear genome and Z chromosome trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." captionText-1="Figure 12. Mitochondrial genome and COI barcode trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677257" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677259" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3677257/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3677259/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Fig. 11–12</figureCitation>
). Keys to J. 
<quantity box="[1262,1354,330,354]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.6266" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" unit="in" value="37.9">37.9 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans (1955)</bibRefCitation>
, but very variable in hindwing patterns, from virtually brown unspotted to pale cream with brown-yellow veins and several central black spots surrounded by yellow or brown. Diagnosed by male genitalia with uncus not protruding from tegumen, very broad caudad with tiny knob-like arms on the side, uncus together with tegumen almost square in dorsal view, valva with very narrow extended hook-shaped harpe like no other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[731,866,490,514]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Hesperiini">Hesperiini</taxonomicName>
. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly274.33.1:A430C, aly2202.27.1:C668A, aly 
<date box="[963,1072,522,546]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" value="2613-03-02">2613.3.2</date>
:A2043C, aly 
<date box="[1222,1331,522,546]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" value="2613-03-02">2613.3.2</date>
:C2248A, aly587.20.1:T1522C.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="31" type="etymology">
