<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,602,626]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a feminine noun in the nominative singular, containing the first four letters of the 
<typeStatus box="[268,321,635,659]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">type</typeStatus>
species name.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[192,707,682,707]" box="[192,707,682,707]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,432,682,706]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Species included.</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus box="[553,606,683,707]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[192,822,730,755]" box="[192,822,730,755]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,380,730,754]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
